h, failing in her pursuit of a third gold in the French capital thissummer.\", \"from\": 343, \"to\": 537, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 511, \"end\": 517, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.8962395798794826, \"rank\": 0.09765574838869978, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"her composure\", \"from\": 377, \"to\": 390}, {\"ngram\": \"a fifth-placed finish\", \"from\": 442, \"to\": 463}, {\"ngram\": \"her pursuit\", \"from\": 476, \"to\": 487}, {\"ngram\": \"a third gold\", \"from\": 491, \"to\": 503}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Alice D'Amato capitalised on Biles' rare off-day to becomeItaly's first ever Olympic champion in women's gymnastics with a score of 14.366 and her compatriot, Manila Esposito, finished third on the leaderboard to get her hands on bronze.\", \"from\": 539, \"to\": 776, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 539, \"end\": 552, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alice_D'Amato\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alice D'Amato\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alice_D'Amato\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alice_D'Amato\"}, {\"begin\": 698, \"end\": 704, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manila\", \"score\": 0.9935143047379288, \"rank\": 0.006528030507782315, \"text\": \"Manila\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manila\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manila\"}, {\"begin\": 705, \"end\": 713, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phil_Esposito\", \"score\": 0.9999999880137694, \"rank\": 1.1986415628375297e-08, \"text\": \"Esposito\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q11774891\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phil_Esposito\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phil_Esposito\"}]